// calculator.mas
/ A MARIE assembly calculator; It accepts a string input, ends with "=?";
/ Extracts 2 operands, integer X and Y, and user defined operator;
/ Accepted operator: '+', '-', '*', '/' (acceptable operators can be redefined from ascii table)
/ Then, perform arithmetic calculation, Output to "output log" and "16x16 Display".

/ Calling SubInputAndExtractOperandsAndOperator subroutine.
JnS SubInputAndExtractOperandsAndOperator

/ Calling SubCal subroutine.
JnS SubCal

/ Calling SubTextOutput subroutine.
JnS SubTextOutput

/ Calling SubClearDisplay subroutine.
JnS SubClearDisplay

/ Calling SubPaintChar subroutine.
Load DigitFontAddr
Add NEXTDIGIT 
Store PaintCharCharacter 
Load PIXELOFROW2COL2 
Store PaintCharDisplay 
JnS SubPaintChar 

/ Calling SubPrintCalResultToDisplay subroutine.
JnS SubPrintCalResultToDisplay

/ End of main program.
Halt

// Helpful subroutines for main program

/ Multiply current input digit by 10
SubMul10,	HEX 0
			Store MulTmp
			Add MulTmp
			Store MulTmp
			Add MulTmp
			Add MulTmp
			Add MulTmp
			Add MulTmp / Build multiple digits integer input
			JumpI SubMul10
			
MulTmp,	DEC 0

/ Negate X if X < 0
CheckNegativeX,	HEX 0
				Load NegativeXFlag
				SkipCond 800
				JumpI CheckNegativeX
				Jump NegateX
				
				NegateX,	Load ZERO
							Subt X
							Store X
				JumpI CheckNegativeX

/ Negate Y if Y < 0
CheckNegativeY,	HEX 0
				Load NegativeYFlag
				SkipCond 800
				JumpI CheckNegativeY
				Jump NegateY
				
				NegateY,	Load ZERO
							Subt Y
							Store Y
				JumpI CheckNegativeY

/ Addition
SubAdd, HEX 0
		Load X
		Add Y
		Store Result
		JumpI SubAdd

/ Subtraction
SubSubt, 	HEX 0
			Load X
			Subt Y
			Store Result
			JumpI SubSubt

/ Multiplication
SubMul, HEX 0
		Load ONE
		Subt NegativeYFlag
		SkipCond 400
		Jump Mul
		Jump SetPositiveY

		/ Set Y to positive for to get positive value
		SetPositiveY,	Load Y
						Subt Y
						Subt Y
						Store Y
						Jump Mul

		/ Repeat CheckAddition until Y - Counter =  0
		Mul,	Load Y
				Subt Counter 
				SkipCond 400
				Jump MulAdd
				Load ONE
				Subt NegativeYFlag
				SkipCond 400
				JumpI SubMul
				Jump NegateMulResult
			
				MulAdd, Load Result
						Add X
						Store Result
						Load Counter
						Add ONE
						Store Counter
						Jump Mul

		/ Negate result if X or Y is negative
		NegateMulResult,	Load Result
							Subt Result
							Subt Result
							Store Result
							JumpI SubMul
						
/ Division
SubDiv,     HEX 0		
            / Check X is positive or negative
            CheckX,	Load ONE
		            Subt NegativeXFlag
		            SkipCond 400         
		            Jump XIsPositive         
		            Jump XIsNegative          

			/ case: X > 0
			XIsPositive,    Load ONE
				            Subt NegativeYFlag
				            SkipCond 400
				            Jump AbsX				/ Y > 0
				            Jump SetNegativeFlag	/ Y < 0

			/ case: X is negative
			XIsNegative,    Load ONE
							Store NegativeResultFlag
				            Subt NegativeYFlag
				            SkipCond 400  
				            Jump SetNegativeFlag 	/ Y > 0
							
							/ X and Y < 0, division result > 0
							Clear
							Store NegativeResultFlag
				            Jump AbsX

			/ Define negative result is true
			SetNegativeFlag,	Load ONE
						        Store NegativeResultFlag
						        Jump AbsX
				
			/ Set positive X and positive Y for division	
			AbsX,	Load ONE
					Subt NegativeXFlag
				    SkipCond 400
				    Jump AbsY
				    Load ZERO
			        Subt X
			        Store X

			AbsY,	Load ONE
					Subt NegativeYFlag
			        SkipCond 400
			        Jump StartDivision
			        Load ZERO
			        Subt Y
			        Store Y

			/ Begin division
			StartDivision,  Load X
				            Store Remainder
				            Clear
				            Store Result

			/ End division if Remainder is negative
			DivLoop,    Load Remainder
			            Subt Y
			            SkipCond 000
			            Jump DivSubt
						Jump SetResult

			/ Store incremented, temporary result
			DivSubt,	Store Remainder
				        Load Result
				    	Add ONE
				        Store Result
				        Jump DivLoop
			
			/ Check result should be negated or not
			SetResult,  Load NegativeResultFlag
						SkipCond 800         
						JumpI SubDiv
							            
						/ Negate result then end division
						Load ZERO
						Subt Result
						Store Result
						JumpI SubDiv

/ Check if screen width has been filled (3 characters max)
CheckScreenFull, HEX 0
                 Load CharColCount
                 Subt THREE        / Change from FOUR to THREE
                 SkipCond 000      / If AC < 0 (count < 3), skip reset
                 JnS RefreshDisplay
                 JumpI CheckScreenFull

/ Give space to each digit display (3px width + 1px gap)
SetSpaceForDigits,	HEX 0
					Load CurrentPos
					Add FOUR         / Move cursor 4 pixels
					Store CurrentPos
					
					/ Increment character counter
					Load CharColCount
					Add ONE
					Store CharColCount
					JumpI SetSpaceForDigits

/ Give space to 4-pixel wide letter display
SetSpaceForLetter,	HEX 0
					Load CurrentPos
					Add FIVE         / Move cursor 5 pixels (4 for char + 1 space)
					Store CurrentPos
					
					/ Increment character counter
					Load CharColCount
					Add ONE
					Store CharColCount
					
					JumpI SetSpaceForLetter

CurrentPos,		DEC 0
CharColCount,	DEC 0

/ Clear screen and reset pointers
RefreshDisplay,	HEX 0
				JnS SubDelay         / Wait so user can read result
				JnS SubClearDisplay  / Clear the 16x16 grid
                Load ScreenStart
				Add ONE              / Start at the first available pixel
                Store CurrentPos
                Clear
                Store CharColCount   / Reset counter to 0
                JumpI RefreshDisplay

/ Modulo 10, returns Quotient and ModRemainder
Mod10,	HEX 0
		Clear
		Store Quotient
		ModL1,	Load ArgX
		        Subt TEN
		        Skipcond 000
		        Jump ModNext
		        Jump ModDone
		ModNext,	Store ArgX
		            Load Quotient
		            Add ONE
		            Store Quotient
		            Jump ModL1
	    ModDone,	Load ArgX
	                Store ModRemainder
	                JumpI Mod10

ArgX,              	DEC 0
Quotient,      		DEC 0

/ Define digit address to print
GetDigitAddr,	HEX 0
				Load DigitFontAddr
				Store Target
	            Load PrintVal
	            Store Tmp
				MultLoop,	Load Tmp
				            Skipcond 800
				            Jump DoneMult
				            Subt ONE
				            Store Tmp
				            Load Target
				            Add FIFTEEN     
				            Store Target
				            Jump MultLoop
				DoneMult,	JumpI GetDigitAddr

Tmp,		DEC 0
Target, 	DEC 0
PrintVal,	DEC 0

/ Delay 500ms before clear screen
SubDelay,	HEX 0
            Load DelayTime
            Store DelayCounter
        	DelayLoop,	Load DelayCounter
	                    Subt ONE
	                    Store DelayCounter
	                    SkipCond 400
	                    Jump DelayLoop
	                    JumpI SubDelay
					
DelayCounter,	DEC 0
DelayTime,      DEC 500

///
/// subroutine: SubInputAndExtractOperandsAndOperator
///

// Accepted input format: "{operand1}{operator}{operand2}=?" (can include negative values)
SubInputAndExtractOperandsAndOperator, HEX 0

	/ Get input, check question mark before end input if is '='
	GetInputX,	Input
				Store Chr
				Subt Equal
				SkipCond 400
				Jump CheckSignX
				Jump EndInput

	GetInputY,	Input
				Store Chr
				Subt Equal
				SkipCond 400
				Jump CheckSignY
				Jump EndInput

	/ Check negative value
	CheckSignX,	Load Chr
				Subt Minus
				SkipCond 400
				Jump NotNegative
				Jump IsNegativeX

	CheckSignY,	Load Chr
				Subt Minus
				SkipCond 400
				Jump NotNegative
				Jump IsNegativeY

	/ Negative value found
	IsNegativeX,	Load ONE
					Store NegativeXFlag
					Jump GetOperand

	IsNegativeY,	Load ONE
					Store NegativeYFlag
					Jump GetOperand

	/ Input integer
	GetOperand,	Input
				Store Chr
				Subt Equal
				SkipCond 400
				Jump CheckOperator
				Jump EndInput

	/ Positive value, set Operator if input any character
	NotNegative,	Load Chr
					Subt ASCII_0
					SkipCond 000
					Jump IsDigit
					Jump SetOperator

	/ Check is X, Y integer
	IsDigit,	Load Chr
				Subt ASCII_0
				Store TmpDigit
				Load FlagOperandY
				SkipCond 400
				Jump UpdateOperandY
				Jump UpdateOperandX

	/ Update integer for 1 digit or more
	UpdateOperandX,	Load X
					JnS SubMul10
					Store Test
					
					Load Test
					Add TmpDigit
					Store X
					Jump GetOperand

	UpdateOperandY,	Load Y
					JnS SubMul10
					Store Test
					
					Load Test
					Add TmpDigit
					Store Y
					Jump GetInputY

	/ Check operator in input character
	CheckOperator,	Load Chr
					Subt ASCII_0
					SkipCond 000
					Jump IsDigit
					Jump SetOperator

	/ Define Operator
	SetOperator,	Load Chr
					Store Operator
					Load NegativeXFlag
					SkipCond 400
					JnS CheckNegativeX
					Jump SetOperandY

	/ Input 2nd integer, store to Y
	SetOperandY,	Clear
					Store Test
					Load ONE
					Store FlagOperandY
					Jump GetInputY

	/ End input
	EndInput,	JnS CheckNegativeY
				Input
				Store Chr
				Subt QuestionMark
				SkipCond 400
				Jump EndInput
				JumpI SubInputAndExtractOperandsAndOperator 

/ local variables of SubInputAndExtractOperandsAndOperator
Minus,			HEX 2D	/ '-'
ASCII_0,		HEX 30	/ '0'
Equal,			HEX 3D	/ '='
QuestionMark,	HEX 3F  / '?'
Chr,			DEC 0
Test,			Dec 0
TmpDigit,		DEC 0
FlagOperandY,	DEC 0
NegativeXFlag,	DEC 0
NegativeYFlag,	DEC 0

///
/// subroutine: SubCal
///
SubCal, HEX 0

	/ If X or Y = 0: result = 0, end calculation
	Load X
	SkipCond 400
	Jump CheckYIsZero
	JumpI SubCal

	CheckYIsZero,	Load Y
					SkipCond 400 
					Jump CheckAddition
					JumpI SubCal

	/ Check Addition
	CheckAddition,	Load Operator
				Subt CHR_ADD
				SkipCond 400
				Jump CheckSubtraction
				JnS SubAdd
				JumpI SubCal

	/ Check subtraction
	CheckSubtraction,	Load Operator
					Subt CHR_SUBT
					SkipCond 400
					Jump CheckMultiplication
					JnS SubSubt
					JumpI SubCal

	/ Check multiplication
	CheckMultiplication,	Load Operator
							Subt CHR_MUL
							SkipCond 400
							Jump CheckDivision
							JnS SubMul
							JumpI SubCal

	/ Check division
	CheckDivision,	Load Operator
					Subt CHR_DIV
					SkipCond 400
					Jump InvalidOpeator
					JnS SubDiv
					JumpI SubCal

	/ Other operator: Invalid, result = 0
	InvalidOpeator,	Clear
					Store Result
					JumpI SubCal

/ local variables of SubCal
CHR_ADD,	HEX 2B / '+'
CHR_SUBT,	HEX 2D / '-'
CHR_MUL,	HEX 2A / '*'
CHR_DIV,	HEX 2F / '/'
CHR_R,		HEX 52 / 'R'

Counter, 			DEC 0 
NegativeResultFlag,	DEC 0

///
/// subroutine SubTextOutput
///
SubTextOutput, HEX 0

/ The logic
	/ Output result
	Load Result
	Output
	Load Operator
	Subt CHR_DIV
	SkipCond 400 / Check: is calculation a division
	JumpI SubTextOutput
	Jump OutputRemainder

	/ Output remainder (division)
	OutputRemainder,	Load Remainder
						Output
						JumpI SubTextOutput

///
/// Implement your subroutine SubClearDisplay here.
///
SubClearDisplay, HEX 0

/ The logic
	/ Initialise address to fill white to display
    Load ScreenStart
    Store TmpPtr
    Load SIXTYFOUR
    Store Tmp

	/ Start fill white to display
	BeginClear,	Clear
	    		Store Cnt

	/ Fill white to display 4 times
	ClearAll,	Load White     
			    StoreI TmpPtr
			    Load TmpPtr
			    Add ONE
			    Store TmpPtr
			    Load Cnt
			    Add ONE
			    Store Cnt
			    Load Cnt
			    Subt FOUR
			    SkipCond 400
			    Jump ClearAll

	/ Finish up filling the display
	FillDone,	Load Tmp
			    Subt ONE
			    Store Tmp
			    Skipcond 400
			    Jump BeginClear
			    JumpI SubClearDisplay

/ local variables of SubClearDisplay
ScreenStart,	HEX F00
White,       	HEX FFFF

Cnt,			DEC 0
TmpPtr,			DEC 0

///
/// subroutine SubPaintChar
///
/ Parameters of SubPaintChar
PaintCharCharacter, HEX 0  
PaintCharDisplay, HEX 0  
SubPaintChar, HEX 0 
	/ Initialise variables for print digits / letter
	Load ScreenStart    / Start of display memory (F00)
    Add ONE             / Offset for better visibility (F01)
    Store CurrentPos    / Reset cursor to far left 
    
    / 2. Reset character tracking
    Clear
    Store CharColCount  / Reset horizontal count 
    Store IsRemainder   / Clear remainder flag
    Store DigitCount    / Reset digit stack count

	/ If result > 0, extract and print digits 
    Load Result
    Skipcond 000
    Jump PrepValue
	
    / Display negative sign for result < 0. Uses offset 150 (10th index in DigitFontStart)
    Load DigitFontAddr
    Add ONEFIFTY
    Store PaintCharCharacter
    Load CurrentPos
    Store PaintCharDisplay
    JnS CheckScreenFull
    JnS SubPrintCalResultToDisplay
    JnS SetSpaceForDigits
    
    / Extract digits from positive result
    Load ZERO
    Subt Result
    Store Value
    Jump DigitExtract

	/ Copy "result" to "value"
	PrepValue,  Load Result
	            Store Value

	/ Extract digits from positive result
	DigitExtract,   Store StackPtr
	                Clear
	                Store DigitCount

	/ Division and modulo by 10 loop to extract digits from left to right, then print to display
	LoopMod,        Load Value
	                Store ArgX
	                JnS Mod10
	                Load ModRemainder
	                StoreI StackPtr
	                Load StackPtr
	                Add ONE
	                Store StackPtr
	                Load DigitCount
	                Add ONE
	                Store DigitCount
	                Load Quotient
	                Store Value
	                Skipcond 400   
	                Jump LoopMod

	/ If done printing all digits in result, confirm to display remainder for division  
	/ Loop to print each extracted digit
	PrintDigits,    Load DigitCount
	                Skipcond 800     / If no more digits, check remainder
	                Jump CheckRemainderState
	          
	                Load StackPtr
	                Subt ONE
	                Store StackPtr
	                
	                / Refresh check before drawing
	                JnS CheckScreenFull / If full, this resets CurrentPos to F01
	                
	                LoadI StackPtr
	                Store PrintVal
	                JnS GetDigitAddr
	                Load Target
	                Store PaintCharCharacter
	                
	                / CurrentPos is now guaranteed to be correct (Left if just refreshed)
	                Load CurrentPos
	                Store PaintCharDisplay 
	        
	                JnS SubPrintCalResultToDisplay
	                JnS SetSpaceForDigits
	                
	                Load DigitCount
	                Subt ONE
	                Store DigitCount
	                Jump PrintDigits

	/ Confirm to print remainder character and digits to display for division
    CheckRemainderState,	Load IsRemainder
						    Skipcond 400
						    JumpI SubPaintChar

	/ Division found, start printing remainder character and digit from remainder
    Load Operator
    Subt CHR_DIV 
    Skipcond 400
    JumpI SubPaintChar

    Load ONE
    Store IsRemainder

	/ Character display, 'R'. Uses offset 544 (17th index in FontStart for letter R)
    Load FontAddr
    Add FIVEFORTYFOUR
    Store PaintCharCharacter
    Load CurrentPos
    Store PaintCharDisplay
    JnS CheckScreenFull
    JnS SubPrint4x8
    JnS SetSpaceForLetter

	/ Set remainder to "value" to display
    Load Remainder
    Store Value
    Jump DigitExtract

/ local variables of SubPaintChar
Value,             	DEC 0
StackPtr,          	DEC 0
DigitCount,        	DEC 0
IsRemainder,  		DEC 0
ModRemainder,       DEC 0
SavedDivRemainder,	DEC 0

///
/// subroutine: SubPrintCalResultToDisplay (3x5 pixel drawing)
///
SubPrintCalResultToDisplay, HEX 0 

	/ Initialise addresses to print result to display
	Load PaintCharCharacter
    Store PtrChar
    Load PaintCharDisplay
    Store PtrDisp
    Load FIVE
    Store RowCount

	/ Set ColCount to 3, display digit or letter with size of 3x5 
	OuterL,	Load THREE
	    	Store ColCount

	/ If PtrChar < 0 goto next pixel, else draw the pixel for digit
	InnerL,	LoadI PtrChar
		    Skipcond 000      
		    Jump DrawPixel
		    Jump NextPixel

	/ Draw pixel to display digit
	DrawPixel,	Load Black
	    		StoreI PtrDisp    

	/ Goto next pixel to draw next pixel for same digit
	NextPixel,	Load PtrChar
			    Add ONE
			    Store PtrChar
			    Load PtrDisp
			    Add ONE
			    Store PtrDisp
			    Load ColCount
			    Subt ONE
			    Store ColCount
			    Skipcond 400
			    Jump InnerL
			    Load PtrDisp
			    Add THIRTEEN
			    Store PtrDisp
			    Load RowCount
			    Subt ONE
			    Store RowCount
			    Skipcond 400
			    Jump OuterL
			    JumpI SubPrintCalResultToDisplay

///
/// subroutine: SubPrint4x8 (4x8 pixel drawing for standard alphabet)
///
SubPrint4x8, HEX 0 

	/ Initialise addresses to print 4x8 letter to display
	Load PaintCharCharacter
    Store PtrChar
    Load PaintCharDisplay
    Store PtrDisp
    Load EIGHT
    Store RowCount

	/ Set ColCount to 4
	OuterL8,	Load FOUR
	    	    Store ColCount

	InnerL8,	LoadI PtrChar
		        Skipcond 000      
		        Jump DrawPixel8
		        Jump NextPixel8

	DrawPixel8,	Load Black
	    		StoreI PtrDisp    

	NextPixel8,	Load PtrChar
			    Add ONE
			    Store PtrChar
			    Load PtrDisp
			    Add ONE
			    Store PtrDisp
			    Load ColCount
			    Subt ONE
			    Store ColCount
			    Skipcond 400
			    Jump InnerL8
			    Load PtrDisp
			    Add TWELVE
			    Store PtrDisp
			    Load RowCount
			    Subt ONE
			    Store RowCount
			    Skipcond 400
			    Jump OuterL8
			    JumpI SubPrint4x8


/ local variables: SubPrintCalResultToDisplay and SubPrint4x8
Black,		DEC 0
PtrChar,  	DEC 0
PtrDisp, 	DEC 0
RowCount,	DEC 0
ColCount,   DEC 0

///
/// CONSTANTS
///
X,			DEC 0
Operator,	DEC 0
Y,			DEC 0
Result,		DEC 0
Remainder,	DEC 0

/ Integers
ZERO, 		DEC 0
ONE,		DEC 1
THREE,		DEC 3
FOUR,		DEC 4
FIVE,   	DEC 5
EIGHT,      DEC 8
TEN,    	DEC 10
TWELVE,     DEC 12
THIRTEEN,	DEC 13
FIFTEEN,    DEC 15
SIXTYFOUR,	DEC 64
EIGHTY,     DEC 80
ONEFIFTY,   DEC 150
FIVEFORTYFOUR, DEC 544

/ Other data for testing program
PIXELOFROW2COL2, 	HEX 0F11 
NEXTDIGIT,			DEC 15

/ This is the "font", the memory that stores character data for the display.
/ The characters are stored in the order a-z.
/ Each character is 4 pixels wide and 8 pixels high.
/ The data for each character is stored row by row, with each pixel
/ being represented as ONE word that is either FFFF (white) or 0000 (black).
FontAddr, ADR FontStart
FontStart, 	HEX FFFF  / Start of character A 
			HEX 0000
			HEX 0000
			HEX FFFF
			HEX 0000
			HEX FFFF
			HEX FFFF
			HEX 0000
			HEX 0000
			HEX FFFF
			HEX FFFF
			HEX 0000
			HEX 0000
			HEX 0000
			HEX 0000
			HEX 0000
			HEX 0000
			HEX FFFF
			HEX FFFF
			HEX 0000
			HEX 0000
			HEX FFFF
			HEX FFFF
			HEX 0000
			HEX 0000
			HEX FFFF
			HEX FFFF
			HEX 0000
			HEX FFFF
			HEX FFFF
			HEX FFFF
			HEX FFFF
			
			HEX 0000  / Start of character B
			HEX 0000
			HEX 0000
			HEX FFFF
			HEX 0000
			HEX FFFF
			HEX FFFF
			HEX 0000
			HEX 0000
			HEX FFFF
			HEX FFFF
			HEX 0000
			HEX 0000
			HEX 0000
			HEX 0000
			HEX FFFF
			HEX 0000
			HEX FFFF
			HEX FFFF
			HEX 0000
			HEX 0000
			HEX FFFF
			HEX FFFF
			HEX 0000
			HEX 0000
			HEX 0000
			HEX 0000
			HEX FFFF
			HEX FFFF
			HEX FFFF
			HEX FFFF
			HEX FFFF
			
			HEX FFFF  / Start of character C
			HEX 0000
			HEX 0000
			HEX 0000
			HEX 0000
			HEX FFFF
			HEX FFFF
			HEX FFFF
			HEX 0000
			HEX FFFF
			HEX FFFF
			HEX FFFF
			HEX 0000
			HEX FFFF
			HEX FFFF
			HEX FFFF
			HEX 0000
			HEX FFFF
			HEX FFFF
			HEX FFFF
			HEX 0000
			HEX FFFF
			HEX FFFF
			HEX FFFF
			HEX FFFF
			HEX 0000
			HEX 0000
			HEX 0000
			HEX FFFF
			HEX FFFF
			HEX FFFF
			HEX FFFF
			
			HEX 0000  / Start of character D
			HEX 0000
			HEX 0000
			HEX FFFF
			HEX 0000
			HEX FFFF
			HEX FFFF
			HEX 0000
			HEX 0000
			HEX FFFF
			HEX FFFF
			HEX 0000
			HEX 0000
